        \\--@{"Virtgroup" LINK "VirtgroupClass"}           handles virtual groups
           +--@{"Crawling" LINK "CrawlingClass"}         handles auto-scrolling virtual groups
           +--@{"HexEdit" LINK "HexEditClass"}          hex editor gadget
           +--@{"HTMLview" LINK "HTMLviewClass"}         HTLM 4 virtual group class
           \\--@{"Pkb" LINK "PkbClass"}              piano keyboards

@EndNode

@Node "MCCs"


@{b}MCCs@{ub}
@{u}                                                                 @{uu}


  RxMUI offers an interface to many MUI classes but they are not
  included in RxMUI archive.

  The following is a list of all the MCCs used in RxMUI:

   o BetterBalance.mcc 11.2 (19-6-1998)
   o CManager.mcc 14.8 (7-8-2001)
   o CompactWindow.mcc 12.6 (6-4-1999)
   o Guigfx.mcc 19.2 (18-8-2000)
   o HexEdit.mcc 14.0 (4-5-1998)
   o Icon.mcc 1.1 (4-9-1996)
   o HTMLview.mcc 12.6 (3-1-2000)
   o InfoText.mcc 15.3 (9-2-1998)
   o Lamp.mcc 11.2 (25-6-1997)
   o Mailtext.mcc 19.8 (26-7-1998)
   o MonthNavigator.mcc 16.8 (7-3-2000)
   o MysticView.mcc 13.0 (15-3-2000)
   o NFloattext.mcc 19.46 (29-3-1998)
   o NList.mcc 20.106 (1-7-2002)
   o NListtree.mcc 18.13 (1.7.2002)
   o NListview.mcc 19.63 (11-5-2002)
   o Pkb.mcc 14.6 (23-5-1999)
   o TearOff mccs 14.2 (3-6-2000) 14.3 (9-6-2000)
   o TextEditor.lha 15.9 (21-5-2000)
   o Textinput.mcc 29.5 (22-12-2001)
   o Textinput.mcc 29.5 (22-12-2001)
   o Toolbar.mcc 15.6 (28-2-2000)
   o TransferAnim.mcc 1.5 (23-8-1999)
   o Wheel.mcc 19.0 (29-12-1999)

  The following is a list of all the libraries used in RxMUI:

   o cmanager.library 10.5 (6-10-2001)
   o guigfx.library 17.1 (26-1-2000)
   o mysticview.library 4.2 (1-6-1999)
   o render.library 4.2 (1-6-1999)
   o vaportoolkit.library 15.2 (13-11-2001) (Textinput.mcc badly
     crashes without it!)

@EndNode

@Node ApplicationClass "RxMUI - Application Class"


Area class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "NotifyClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Application class is the main class in RxMUI.

  Any window you create must be added to an Application object.

  Windows may be added to an Application object during the init
  process via the SubWindow attribute.

  The first window may be specified as

      .SubWindow="win"

  or

      .SubWindow.0="win"

  Other windows may be added during the init process as

      .SubWindow.i="win"

  In general, windows may be added to an Application object via
  the @{"Add()" LINK "Add"} function.

  A window can't be opened if it is not added to an Application
  object.

  Your goal is, quite always, to create a tree like this:

  - An Application object which contains
    - A Window object, with contents
      - a Group, called main group, which contains
        - various objects

  See @{"Objects handling" link "ObjectsHandling"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Active@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Author@{fg text}
  S IG

  @{fg shine}Base@{fg text}
  S IG
  Should be supplied if UseARexx=1 or OwnARexx=1

  @{fg shine}Copyright@{fg text}
  S IG

  @{fg shine}Description@{fg text}
  S IG
  Should be supplied if UseCommodities=1

  @{fg shine}DiskObject@{fg text}
  S I
  Name of an icon WITHOUT .info

  @{fg shine}DoubleStart@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}DropObject@{fg text}
  S S
  The name of an object. Note that the attribute is only settable
  and that a previous call to AppMessage() must be done (or
  nothing will happen).

  @{fg shine}ForceQuit@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}HelpFile@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Iconified@{fg text}
  B SGN

  @{fg shine}MenuHelp@{fg text}
  N GN
  Notified when the user presses the help key on a menu item

  @{fg shine}MenuStrip@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Num1@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  An integral user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}Num2@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  An integral user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}Num3@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  An integral user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}OwnARexx@{fg text}
  B I
  It is so bad that we have an ARexx port opened and we can't get
  messages from it. If you specify OwnARexx you get the same port
  that would be opened (it means BASE if SingleTask=1 BASE.X if
  SingleTask=0) but internal in the macro. It means that you have
  to handle all the commands coming to the port, MUI ones too
  (e.g. QUIT)

  @{fg shine}SingleTask@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Sleep@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}String1@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  A string user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}String2@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  A string user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}String3@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  A string user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}Title@{fg text}
  S I
  Should be supplied if UseCommodities=1

  @{fg shine}UseARexx@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}UseCommodities@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Version@{fg text}
  S IG

  @{fg shine}WantARexxCmd@{fg text}
  B I
  This attribute instructs the object to pass any ARexx command
  it receives to its port to the macro via AREXXCMD event.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}About@{fg text}
  [win],[string]
  Shows a little about window. win is a window object name in
  front of which the About window will be opened; it may be
  _first which means the first application opened window string
  is the message to show; if it is not supplied the text to show
  is automatically constructed.

  @{fg shine}ABoutMUI@{fg text}
  [win]
  Shows the About MUI requester. win is a window object name in
  front of which the About MUI window will be opened; it may be
  _first which means the first application opened window.

  @{fg shine}AboutRxMUI@{fg text}
  [win]
  Shows the About RxMUI requester. win is a window object name in
  front of which the ABout RxMUI window will be opened; it may be
  _first which means the first application opened window.

  @{fg shine}InLine@{fg text}
  <fun>,[attribute | TriggerAttribute]

  Used in notifications like:
      call Notify("slider",trigger,value,"app","InLine","parse arg name,value;...",attr)

  When trigger changes to value, fun, an inline ARexx function
  macro, is called;
  its arguments are:
      1. the name of the notifier object
      2. the value of attr; the attribute must be G; a special
         value is TRIGGERATTR that means the triggering
         attribute; if no attribute is supplied, the function
         receives just one argument.

  The function is called in the same process of the running macro
  and so in it there can be used any RxMUI functions on any
  object, but it is called as a separate ARexx macro and HASN'T
  GOT the environment of the running macro (e.g. ala INTEPRET
  command). It means mainly that the existing variables are not
  valid in the function (they just don't exist).

  @{fg shine}InputBuffered@{fg text}
  -

  @{fg shine}Load@{fg text}
  [file | ENV | ENVARC]
  default ENV

  @{fg shine}OpenConfigWindow@{fg text}
  -

  @{fg shine}Return@{fg text}
  <string>,[attr]
  Used only in notifications like
      call Notify("WIN","CLOSEREQUEST","APP","RETURN","HELLO")
      call Notify("CYCLE","ACTIVE","APP","RETURN","TRIGGERATTR")

  @{fg shine}ReturnID@{fg text}
  [QUIT]
  Used only in notifications like
      call Notify("win","CloseRequest","EveryTime","app","ReturnID","quit")
  or
      call Notify("button","pressed",0."app","ReturnID")
  The Application will return the name of the object that
  triggered the notification or the special value QUIT that means
  the Application should be closed. Any other value is a bad one.

  @{fg shine}Save@{fg text}
  [file | ENV | ENVARC]
  default ENV

  @{fg shine}SetVar@{fg text}
  <var>
  Used only in notifications, it sets a var to the value of the
  triggering attribute:
      call Notify("CYCLE","ACTIVE","EVERYTIME","SETVAR","ACT")
  act will always contain the active entry of CYCLE.

  @{fg shine}ShowHelp@{fg text}
  [win],[file],[node],[line/N]
  Show an help file, via the amigaGuide datatype.
  Arguments:
     o win is a Window object name to show the file on the screen
       of which
     o file is the name of the file to show; if not supplied the
       Application HelpFile, if any, is used
     o node is the name of an AmigaGuide node to show
     o line is a line number of node to show

@EndNode

@Node AreaClass "RxMUI - Area Class"


Area class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "NotifyClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  Area class objects are not usefull at all, but Area class
  attribute and methods may be used with any of its subclasses.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Background@{fg text}
  S IS
  One of:
     o None
     o WindowBack
     o RequesterBack
     o ButtonBack
     o ListBack
     o TextBack
     o PropBack
     o PopupBack
     o RegisterBack
     o GroupBack
     o SliderBack
     o PageBack
     o ReadListBack
     o Background
     o Shadow
     o Shine
     o Fill
     o ShadowBack
     o ShadowFill
     o ShadowShine
     o FillBack
     o FillShine
     o ShineBack
     o FillBack2
     o HShineBack
     o HShadowBack
     o HShineShine
     o HShadowShadow
     o MarkShine
     o MarkHalfShine
     o MarkBackground

  @{fg shine}BottomEdge@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}ContextMenu@{fg text}
  S IS
  This is a Menustrip object that is used as context menu. The
  same Menustrip may be used as context menu for many objects;
  the only limitation is that they must be in the same window.
  RxMUI does not check for that! Please be careful.

  @{fg shine}ControlChar@{fg text}
  C ISG
  A char to use as key for the Object. Note that not all the
  classes react to control chars.

  @{fg shine}CycleChain@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}Disabled@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Draggable@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}Dropable@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}EBackground@{fg text}
  M I
  It accepts the same value as Background plus the same format of
  Image class @{"Spec" LINK "ImageClass"} attribute (e.g. "5:images/back.gif"). Remember
  that to set the background of a window you have to simply set
  the background of its root (Contents) object.

  @{fg shine}FillArea@{fg text}
  B IS
  Useless in RxMUI.

  @{fg shine}FixHeight@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}FixHeightTxt@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}FixWidth@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}FixWidthTxt@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Font@{fg text}
  S IS
  One of:
     o Inherit
     o Normal
     o List
     o Tiny
     o Fixed
     o Title
     o Big
     o Button

  @{fg shine}Frame@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o None
     o Button
     o ImageButton
     o Text
     o String
     o ReadList
     o InputList
     o Prop
     o Gauge
     o Group
     o Popup
     o Virtual
     o Slider

  @{fg shine}FramePhantomHoriz@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}FrameTitle@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Height@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}HorizDisappear@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}HorizWeight@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}InnerBottom@{fg text}
  N IG

  @{fg shine}InnerLeft@{fg text}
  N IG

  @{fg shine}InnerRight@{fg text}
  N IG

  @{fg shine}InnerTop@{fg text}
  N IG

  @{fg shine}InputMode@{fg text}
  S I One of:
     o None
     o RelVerify
     o Immediate
     o Toggle

  @{fg shine}LeftEdge@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}MaxHeight@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}MaxWidth@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}Pressed@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}RightEdge@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}Selected@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}ShortHelp@{fg text}
  S ISG

  @{fg shine}ShowMe@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  You should use Add/Remove rather than this.

  @{fg shine}ShowSelState@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Timer@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}TopEdge@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}VertDisappear@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}VertWeight@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}Weight@{fg text}
  N IS

  @{fg shine}Width@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode

