@Node BwinClass "RxMUI - Bwin Class"


Bwin class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "WindowClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  BWin class is used to create beautiful borderless windows.

  BWin class is a subclass of BWin.mcc, so you must have BWin.mcc
  in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AutoShow@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If set to 1, the DragBar, the Size gadget and the Close gadget
  (not yet supported) are shown as the window is active and are
  hidden as the window is inactive. Default 0.

  @{fg shine}Background@{fg text}
  S IS
  See Area/Background

  @{fg shine}DragBarTop@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If set to 1, the DragBar (if available) is placed at the top of
  the window, otherwise it is placed at the left. Default 0.

  @{fg shine}NoClose@{fg text}
  B IG
  If set to 1, you get no Close gadget at all. Default 0. Not yet
  supported.

  @{fg shine}NoCloseItem@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If set to 1, the Close context menu item is disabled. Default
  0. Not yet supported.

  @{fg shine}NoDragBar@{fg text}
  B IG
  If set to 1, you get no DragBar at all. Default 0.

  @{fg shine}NoHideItem@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If set to 1, the Hide context menu item is disabled.
  Default 0.

  @{fg shine}NoSize@{fg text}
  B IG
  If set to 1, you get no Size gadget at all. Default 0.

  @{fg shine}Save@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  Define what to save during Application/Save method and what to
  restore during Application/Load method. A number or one or more
  of:
     o All
     o AutoShow
     o DragBarTop
     o ShowClose
     o ShowDragBar
     o ShowSize

  To save none, set it to 0. Default 0 .

  @{fg shine}ShowClose@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If set to 1, the Close gadget is shown, otherwise it is hidden.
  Default 1. Not yet supported.

  @{fg shine}ShowDragBar@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If set to 1, the DragBar is shown, otherwise it is hidden.
  Default 1.

  @{fg shine}ShowSize@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If set to 1, the Size gadget is shown, otherwise it is hidden.
  Default 1.

  @{fg shine}UserItem@{fg text}
  N GN
  Set and notified to an user item id when it is selected. See
  AddUserItem method.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AddUserItem@{fg text}
  <title>,<id/N>
  Add an user item to the BWin context menu.
  title is the title of the item;
  id is a integral number,0<id<=1024, set in the attribute
  UserItem when the item is selected.

  @{fg shine}RemoveUserItem@{fg text}
  <id/N>
  Remove an user item from the BWin context menu.
  id is the id of the item to remove.

@EndNode

