@Node GfxpicClass "RxMUI - Gfxpic Class"


Gfxpic class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Gfxpic class is used to display datatype pictures.

  Of course, you may give a Gfxpic object a Frame, a Background
  and an InputMode, to make it act like a button.

  Note that disabling a Gfxpic object is not supported in this
  release, so if you need to disable a Gfxpic object, just
  incapsulate it in a group.

  Gfxpic may be used when other graphic classes failed. If you
  cannot show your picture via Bitmap and Picture, try to use
  Gfxpic.

  Gfxpic uses guigfx.library so you must have guigfx.library in
  LIBS: to use it. guigfx.library is copyright of Timm S. Müller.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AlphaPresent@{fg text}
  N G
  Boolean to indicate if the image has an alpha channel Draw B S
  For smooth scaling without removing the object. See Gfxpic.rexx
  example for how to use it.

  @{fg shine}DitherMode@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o FS
     o EDD
     o None
     o Random

  @{fg shine}FreeHoriz@{fg text}
  B I
  The image is horizontal unlimited (free).

  @{fg shine}FreeVert@{fg text}
  B I
  The image is vertical unlimited (free)

  @{fg shine}ImageHeight@{fg text}
  N G
  The real height of the image

  @{fg shine}ImageWidth@{fg text}
  N G
  The real width of the image

  @{fg shine}MaxPens@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}Precision@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o Exact
     o Image
     o Icon
     o Gui

  @{fg shine}Scale@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  It is a positive value, percent factor for scaling.

  @{fg shine}ScaledWidth@{fg text}
  N G
  Width of the scaled image

  @{fg shine}ScaledHeight@{fg text}
  N G
  Height of the scaled image

  @{fg shine}Source@{fg text}
  S I IND
  The source of data. See SourceType. Note that this attribute
  have to be always supplied.

  @{fg shine}Transparent@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If the image has an alpha mask or a transparent color, it
  makes that transparent

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode

@Node GIFAnimClass "RxMUI - GIFAnim Class"


GIFAnim class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The GIFAnim class is used to display gif pictures and
  animations.

  GIFAnim class is a subclass of GIFAnim.mcc, so you must have
  GIFAnim.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Anim@{fg text}
  B IGN
  If 0 the animation is not started. Default 1.

  @{fg shine}Current@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  The current frame of the animation.

  @{fg shine}Decoded@{fg text}
  B GN
  1 when the animation is being decoded.

  @{fg shine}File@{fg text}
  S I IND
  The name of the file to load. It may be max 256 chars long.

  @{fg shine}Fallback@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1 and the specified file doesn't exist or it is not a
  gif file, the object still setups and Invalid is set to 1. If
  set to 0 and the specified file can't be parsed for any reason,
  the object refuses to setup. Default 1.

  @{fg shine}Invalid@{fg text}
  B GN
  1 when the file can't be parsed for any reasone and Fallback was
  1.

  @{fg shine}Pics@{fg text}
  N G
  The number of the frames of the animation. It is correct only
  after all the frames has been decoded.

  @{fg shine}Precision@{fg text}
  I M
  The precision to use when obtaining pens. A number or one of:
     o GUI
     o icon
     o Image
     o Exact

  @{fg shine}Scale@{fg text}
  N I
  Scale factor in the range 1...16383. Of course, only a small
  subset of the above is really usable.

  @{fg shine}Sync@{fg text}
  B I
  Set it to 1 if you want, for some strange reason, the decoding
  process to be sync. Note that the object will not setup till
  the whole file has been decoded. Default 0.

  @{fg shine}Transparent@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  The picture is drawn with the transparent mask, if available.
  Default 1.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}First@{fg text}
  -
  Move to the first frame.


  @{fg shine}Last@{fg text}
  -
  Move to the last frame.


  @{fg shine}Next@{fg text}
  -
  Move to the next frame.

  @{fg shine}Play@{fg text}
  [options]
  Controls the animation. options is a number or
     o Off - Pause the animation
  or one or more of:
     o On - Start the animation
     o Once - Start a single animation-loop
     o Rewind - Start the animation from the first frame

  @{fg shine}Pred@{fg text}
  -
  Move to the previous frame.

@EndNode

@Node GroupClass "RxMUI - Group Class"


Group class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Group class is used to create a set of objects.

  A group object can only be added to a window or to another
  group object. HGroup is identical to Group class, but its
  istances are always horiz groups.

  See @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}ActivePage@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  Valid only if PageMode is 1; a number or one of:
     o Advance
     o First
     o Last
     o Next
     o Prev

  @{fg shine}Columns@{fg text}
  N IS

  @{fg shine}Forward@{fg text}
  B S

  @{fg shine}Horiz@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}HorizSpacing@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}PageMode@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Rows@{fg text}
  N IS

  @{fg shine}SameHeight@{fg text}
  N IS

  @{fg shine}SameSize@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}SameWidth@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Spacing@{fg text}
  N IS

  @{fg shine}VertSpacing@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}ExitChange@{fg text}
  -

  @{fg shine}InitChange@{fg text}
  -

  @{fg shine}Sort@{fg text}
  {obj}

  You may list up to 13 children of the group to be sorted in the
  specified order. If you need to sort more than 13 objects, use
  SortStem . SortStem <stem> Specify in stem.0,... the children
  to sort.

  How to dynamically add/remove objects:
    1. Enter the Change phase:
       call DoMethod("group","InitChange")

    2. Remove the obsolete object (if needed):
       call Remove("obsolete_obj")

    3. Add the new object (if needed):
       call Add("group","new_obj")

    4. Exit the Change phase:
       call DoMethod("group","ExitChange")

@EndNode

@Node GuigfxClass "RxMUI - Guigfx Class"


Guigfx class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Guigfx class is a subclass of Area class and it is used to
  display picture files via guigfx.library.

  Guigfx is a subclass of Guigfx.mcc so you must have Guigfx.mcc
  in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. Guigfx.mcc is copyright of Matthias
  Bethke.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}FileName@{fg text}
  S I
  Name of the picture file to show

  @{fg shine}Quality@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Low
     o Medium
     o High
     o Best

  @{fg shine}ScaleMode@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number, None or a combination of:
     o ScaleUp
     o ScaleDown
     o ScaleFree
     o KAPicture
     o KAScreen

  @{fg shine}Transparency@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or a combination of:
     o Mask
     o RGB

  @{fg shine}TransparentColor@{fg text}
  N IS
  A 4 bytes max long packed chars string ('00rrggbb'x)

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

