@Node IFListClass "RxMUI - IFList Class"


IFList class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "ListClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The IFList class is used to create a list of the available
  communication interfaces.

  Anytime a IFList object is going to be rendered in a Listview,
  the interfaces list is re-read.

  IFlist can only be used with Listview objects.

  The best performances of IFlist are obtained with Miami.

  See @{"List" LINK "ListClass"} @{"Listview" LINK "ListviewClass"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Inet@{fg text}
  N I
  If set to 0, all the interfaces found are shown.
  If omitted or set to 1, just UP interfaces are shown.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Rebuild@{fg text}
  -
  Re-reads the interfaces list.

@EndNode

@Node ImageClass "RxMUI - Image Class"


Image class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Image class is a subclass of Area class and it is used to
  display MUI builtin images.

  Of course, you may give an Image object a Frame, a Background
  and an Inputmode, to make it act like a button

  See @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}FontMatch@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}FontMatchHeight@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}FontMatchWidth@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}FreeHoriz@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}FreeVert@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Spec@{fg text}
  S I
  The type of the image.
  You may use a string or a number here.
  The string may be one of:
     o WindowBack
     o RequesterBack
     o ButtonBack
     o ListBack
     o TextBack
     o PropBack
     o PopupBack
     o SelectedBack
     o ListCursor
     o ListSelect
     o ListSelCur
     o ArrowUp
     o ArrowDown
     o ArrowLeft
     o ArrowRight
     o CheckMark
     o RadioButton
     o Cycle
     o PopUp
     o PopFile
     o PopDrawer
     o PropKnob
     o Drawer
     o HardDisk
     o Disk
     o Chip
     o Volume
     o RegisterBack
     o Network
     o Assign
     o TapePlay
     o TapePlayBack
     o TapePause
     o TapeStop
     o TapeRecord
     o GroupBack
     o SliderBack
     o SliderKnob
     o TapeUp
     o TapeDown
     o PageBack
     o ReadListBack
     o Background
     o Shadow
     o Shine
     o Fill
     o ShadowBack
     o ShadowFill
     o ShadowShine
     o FillBack
     o FillShine
     o ShineBack
     o FillBack2
     o HShineBack
     o HShadowBack
     o HShineShine
     o HShadowShadow
     o Markshine
     o MarkHalfShine
     o MarkBackground

  Or a MUI image specification:
     o 0:<x> where <x> is an integer identifying a builtin pattern
     o 2:<r>,<g>,<b> where <r>, <g> <b> are 32-bit RGB color values specified
       as 8-digit hex string (e.g. 00000000 or ffffffff). Kick 2.x users will
       get an empty image
     o 3:<n> where <n> is the name of an external boopsi image class
     o 4:<n> where <n> is the name of an external MUI brush
     o 5:<n> where <n> is the name of an external picture file that should be
       loaded with datatypes. Kick 2.x users will get an empty image
     o 6:<x> where <x> is an integer identifying a preconfigured
       image/background

  @{fg shine}State@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o Normal
     o Selected
     o Disabled
     o Busy
     o Indeterminate
     o InactiveNormal
     o InactiveSelected
     o InactiveDisabled
     o SelectedDisabled

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode

@Node InfoTextClass "RxMUI - InfoText Class"


InfoText class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "TextClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The InfoText class is used to show an information text.

  InfoText is a subclass of InfoText.mcc so you must have
  InfoText.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. InfoText.mcc is
  copyright of Benny Kjćr Nielsen.

  Note that any attribute of Text class, e.g. Preparse may be
  used with InfoText.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Contents@{fg text}
  S SGN
  The actual contents of the InfoText. Note that after
  ExpirationPeriod, it expires and InfoText shows FallBackText or
  an empty string.

  @{fg shine}ExpirationPeriod@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Milliseconds after which Contents expires, default 4000.

  @{fg shine}FallBackText@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  Text to show after expiration.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Timeout@{fg text}
  -
  Force expiration of Contents.

@EndNode

