@Node ListClass "RxMUI - List Class"


List class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The List class is used to manipulate lists.

  A list object is not a Listview: it is the object a Listview
  renders.

  A List object can only be added to a Listview object at
  Listview creation time.

  See @{"Listview" LINK "ListviewClass"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Active@{fg text}
  M ISGN
  G2N A number or one of:
     o Bottom
     o Down
     o Off
     o PageDown
     o PageUp
     o Top
     o Up

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry@{fg text}
  S GN
  As Active, but as the value of the active entry

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry0@{fg text}
  S GN
  The value of the columun number 0 of the active entry

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry1@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry2@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry3@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry4@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry5@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry6@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry7@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry8@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry9@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}AdjustHeight@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}AdjustWidth@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}AutoVisible@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}Case@{fg text}
  B I
  Sets comparation mode (0 is the default)

  @{fg shine}DefaultInsertPos@{fg text}
  M IS
  A number or one of:
     o Active
     o Default (Default)
     o Bottom
     o Sorted
     o Top

  Entries supplied at Init time or via AddStem or ClearAddStem
  are inserted at this position.

  If this attribute is not supplied or its value is Default,
  entries are inserted:
     o Sorted - if DragSortable is 1
     o At the bottom - otherwise

  @{fg shine}DragSortable@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}DropMark@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}Entries@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}First@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}Format@{fg text}
  S ISG

  @{fg shine}Image@{fg text}
  S I
  See Images in lists

  @{fg shine}InsertPosition@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}List@{fg text}
  S I
  A name of an ARexx stem where to read entries

  @{fg shine}MinColCompare@{fg text}
  N I
  Specify the minimum column number that affects the sorting. It
  is specially usefull if the first column of the list contains
  an image specification.

  @{fg shine}MinLineHeight@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}Names@{fg text}
  S I
  A string of entries separated by a ,

  @{fg shine}NumSelected@{fg text}
  N G
  The number of the selected entries

  @{fg shine}Quiet@{fg text}
  B SG

  @{fg shine}ShowDropMark@{fg text}
  B ISG
  For compatibility reasons, use ShowDropMarks

  @{fg shine}ShowDropMarks@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}SortFormat@{fg text}
  S ISG
  Here you may specify a sort Format String to control some
  sorting options. The string may contain one entry for each
  column of the list. Entries are seperated by commas, one entry
  is parsed via dos.library/ReadArgs().

  The template for a single entry is:
  C=COL/K/N,NUM/S,CASE/S

  where:

  o COL
    This value adjusts the number of the current column. Defaults
    to current entry number (0,1,...).

  o NUM
    An integral number comparation is to be applied to this
    column.

  o CASE
    A string case comparation is to be applied to this column.

  Note that:

  1. Default value is an empty string.

  2. If one column is omitted, it's value is cleared.

  3. Numeric comparation is also controlled by NumSort attribute.

  4. Case comparation is also controlled by Case attribute.

  5. Entries for columns that doesn't exist are ignored.

  Example:

  Let's suppose you created a List with 3 col, First, Second and
  Third, where First is to be nocase-sorted, Second is to be
  case-sorted and Third is to be num-sorted, just set (init)
  SortFormat to "CASE,,NUM"

  @{fg shine}Title@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Visible@{fg text}
  N N

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AddStem@{fg text}
  <stemName/V>,[pos]
  Add the entries defined in stem to the list.
  mode is one of:
     o Active
     o Default
     o Bottom
     o Sorted
     o Top
  See DefaultInsertPos

  @{fg shine}Clear@{fg text}
  -
  Clear the list.

  @{fg shine}ClearAddStem@{fg text}
  <stemName/V>,[pos]
  As AddStem, but clear the list before adding
  the entries.
  mode is one of:
     o Active
     o Default
     o Bottom
     o Sorted
     o Top
  See DefaultInsertPos

  @{fg shine}Exchange@{fg text}
  <entry1>,<entry2>
  Exchanges 2 entries.
  entry1 is a number or one of:
     o Active
     o Bottom
     o Top
  entry2 is a number or one of:
     o Active
     o Bottom
     o Next
     o Previous
     o Top

  @{fg shine}GetEntries@{fg text}
  <stemName>
  The method writes in stem.num the number of the entries and in
  stem.0,... stem.i (i=stem.num-1) the entries:
      call DoMethod("list","GetEntries","entries")
      do i=0 to entries.num-1
          say entries.i
      end

  @{fg shine}GetEntry@{fg text}
  <pos>,<var>
  Get an entry.
  pos is a number or Active

  @{fg shine}GetSelected@{fg text}
  <stem>
  The method writes in stem.num the number of the selected
  entries and in stem.0,... stem.i (i=stem.num-1) the entries:
      do i=0 to sel.num-1
          say sel.i
      end

  @{fg shine}Insert@{fg text}
  <entry>,[pos]
  Insert an entry in a list.
  pos is a number or one of:
     o Active
     o Bottom (Default)
     o Sorted
     o Top

  @{fg shine}Jump@{fg text}
  [pos]
  Jump to an entry, making it visible.
  pos is a number or one of
     o Active (Default)
     o Bottom
     o Down
     o Top

  @{fg shine}Remove @{fg text}
  [pos]
  Remove an entry.
  pos is a number or one of
     o Active (Default)
     o First
     o Last
     o Selected

  @{fg shine}ReplaceCol@{fg text}
  <pos>,<col>,<value>
  Replace the contents of the col column of the
  pos entry with value.
  pos is a number of Active.

  @{fg shine}Select @{fg text}
  [pos],[type],[var/S]
  Select entries.

  pos is a number or one of:
     o Active (Default)
     o All

  type is a number or one of:
     o Ask
     o On
     o Off
     o Toggle (Default)

  If type is Ask the third argument must be supplied and must be
  a valid ARexx var name: it will contain the number of the
  selected entries.

  @{fg shine}Sort@{fg text}
  -
  Sort the entries of the list.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

  @{b}Insertion and sorting@{ub}

  Insertion means adding entries at init time and adding entries
  with AddStem and ClearAddStem methods.

  Insertion is ruled by the following attributes:
  o DefaultInsertPos
  o DragSortable

  At init time, if DefaultInsertPos is specified ad it is not
  Default, entries are inserted at the position there specified,
  otherwise if DragSortable is 1, entries are inserted Sorted,
  otherwise entries are inserted at the bottom.

  The above applies as well, when adding entries with AddStem and
  ClearAddStem.

  Sorting is ruled by:
  o SortType
  o SortFormat;

  SortType specifies the sorting criterium: no sort, the number
  of the column that rules the sort, a reverse order.

  SortFormat specifies options for each column of the List.

  Note that SortType default value is OFF. It means that no
  sorting applies and entries are inserted not sorted (usually at
  the bottom).

@EndNode

@Node ListtreeClass "RxMUI - Listtree Class"


Listtree class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "ListClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Listtree class is used to manipulate trees of lists.

  A Listtree object can only be added to a Listview object at
  Listview creation time.

  Despite Listtree class is declared to be subclass of List
  class, no List attribute and method may be used with a Listtree
  object.

  Listtree is a subclass of Listtree.mcc so you must have
  Listtree.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. Listtree.mcc is
  copyright of Klaus Melchior.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}ActiveID@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  This attribute indicates the active entry in a Listtree. The
  possible values are non negative integer, where 0 means no
  active entry, >0 means there is an active entry. Note that any
  reference to an entry is made by ActiveID !!!.

  @{fg shine}ActiveName@{fg text}
  S ISG
  The name of the active entry

  @{fg shine}DoubleClick@{fg text}
  B GN
  G2N

  @{fg shine}DragDropSort@{fg text}
  B IS

  @{fg shine}DropMark@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}DropType@{fg text}
  S G
  One of:
     o Above
     o Below
     o Onto
     o Sorted
     o None

  @{fg shine}EmptyNodes@{fg text}
  B IS

  @{fg shine}Format@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Quiet@{fg text}
  B IS

  @{fg shine}Title@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}TreeColumn@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Clear@{fg text}
  -
  Clear the whole Listtree.

  @{fg shine}Close@{fg text}
  -
  Closes the whole Listtree

  @{fg shine}FindName@{fg text}
  <var>,<name>,[list],[flags]
  Gets an entry by name.

  Arguments:
     o var - where to store results
     o name - the name of the entry to find
     o list - where to search; a positive integral number or one
       of:
        o Active
        o Root (Default)
     o flags - one or more of:
        o Activate
        o SameLevel
        o Selected
        o StartNode
        o Visible

  @{fg shine}GetEntry@{fg text}
  <var>,[id]
  Gets an entry by id.

  Arguments:
     o var - where to store results
     o id - a positive integral number or Active (Default)

  The method writes in var the entry and in the fields:
     o .Frozen
     o .List
     o .NoSign
     o .Open
     o .Selected
  an ARexx boolean

  @{fg shine}GetEntry2@{fg text}
  <var>,[id],[pos],[flags]
  Relative-gets an entry by id.

  Arguments:
     o var - where to store results
     o id - a positive integral number or one of:
        o Active
        o Root (Default)
     o pos - id-relative position of the node to get; one of:
        o Head (Default)
        o Tail
        o Active
        o Next
        o Previous
        o Parent
     o flags - one or more of:
        o SameLevel
        o Visible

  The method writes in var the entry and in the fields:
     o .Frozen
     o .List
     o .NoSign
     o .Open
     o .Selected
  an ARexx boolean

  @{fg shine}Insert@{fg text}
  <entry>,[list],[prev],[flags],[name]
  @Insert an entry.

  Arguments:
     o entry - the entry to insert
     o list - the node which list is used to insert the entry; a positive
       integral number or one of:
        o Root
        o Active (Default)
     o list - the node which is the predecessor of the node to
       insert; a positive integral number or one of:
        o Head
        o Tail
        o Active (Default)
        o Sorted
     o flags - one or more of:
        o Open
        o List
        o Frozen
        o NoSign
        o NextNode
        o Active
        o Visible
     o name - the name of the entry

  @{fg shine}Open@{fg text}
  -
  Opens the whole Listtree

  @{fg shine}Remove@{fg text}
  [id],[what]
  Removes and entry.

  Arguments:
     o id - the entry to remove; a positive integral number or
       one of:
        o Active
        o Root (default)
     o what - what to remove with id; one of:
        o Head
        o Tail
        o Active
        o All
  Note that if what is not supplied, all id is removed.

  @{fg shine}Sort@{fg text}
  [id],[flags]
  Sorts entries.

  Arguments:
     o id - what to sort; a positive integral number or one of:
        o Active
        o Root (Default)
     o flags - one of:
        o Open

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Examples@{ub}

  1. Static creation
     list.Frame="InputList"
     list.Format="BAR,"
     list.Title="Name|Phone"
      list.0="Friends"; list.0.flags="close"; list.0.list="am"
       am.0="Frank|0864845111"; am.0.name="Frank"
       am.2="University"; am.2.name="uni"; am.2.type="tree"; am.2.flags="close"
       am.2.list="uni"
        uni.0="Mary"; uni.0.name="Mary"
        uni.1="Jhon"
        uni.2="Profs"; uni.2.flags="list"
       am.1="Robert"
      list.1="Computer Shop"

  2. Dynamic insertion
     list.Frame="InputList"
     list.Format="BAR,"
     list.Title="Name|Phone"
     ...
     call set("list","Quiet",1)
     call DoMethod("list","Insert","Friends","root",,"List"); friends=rc
      call DoMethod("list","Insert","Franck|0864845111",friends,,,"A")
      call DoMethod("list","Insert","University",friends,,"List","uni"); uni=rc
       call DoMethod("list","Insert","Mary",uni,,,"Mary")
       call DoMethod("list","Insert","Jhon",uni)
       call DoMethod("list","Insert","Profs",uni,,"list")
      call DoMethod("list","Insert","Robert",friends)
     call DoMethod("list","Insert","Computer Shop","root")
     call set("list","Quiet",0)

  3. How to get all the entries of a Listtree (with its structure)
     call printList("root",0)
     ...
     printList: procedure
     parse arg l,s
         call DoMethod("Listtree","GetEntry2","e",l,"head")
         do while rc
             say copies(" ",s) || "Name:"e.name "Value:"e "ID:"e.id "IsList:"e.list
             if e.list then call printList(e.id,s+1)
             call DoMethod("Listtree","GetEntry2","e",e.id,"next")
         end
         return

@EndNode

@Node ListviewClass "RxMUI - Listview Class"


Listview class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "GroupClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Listview class is used to create Listview.

  A Listview object is not a list: it is the graphic object that
  renders a list object.

  Once you created a Listview object, you can set/get any
  attribute and use any method of its list object directly to the
  Listview. Actually there can be added to a Listview: Floattext,
  List and Dirlist objects.

  See @{"List" LINK "ListClass"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AutoDefault@{fg text}
  B I
  Set the DefaultObject of the window the object belongs to this
  Listview. Usefull when the Listview is in Popobject/Popstring

  @{fg shine}ClickColumn@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}DefClickColumn@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}DoubleClick@{fg text}
  B IGN

  @{fg shine}DragType@{fg text}
  S IS
  One of:
     o None
     o Immediate

  @{fg shine}Input@{fg text}
  B IS

  @{fg shine}List@{fg text}
  S I
  The name of a list object

  @{fg shine}MultiSelect@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o None
     o Default

  @{fg shine}Names@{fg text}
  S I
  A string of entries separated by a ,

  @{fg shine}ScrollerPos@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}SelectChange@{fg text}
  S GN
  One of :
     o None
     o Default
     o Left

  @{fg shine}UseWinBorder@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o None
     o Left
     o Right
     o Bottom

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode

@Node MailtextClass "RxMUI - Mailtext Class"


Mailtext class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "NListClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Mailtext class is used to display e-mail text.

  Mailtext class is a subclass of NList class and can only be
  added to NListview object . Mailtext class is a subclass of
  Mailtext.mcc, so you must have Mailtext.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to
  use it. Mailtext.mcc is copyright Olaf Peters.

  See @{"NList" LINK "NListClass"} @{"NListview" LINK "NListviewClass"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}CopyToClip@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}ForbidContextMenu@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Mail@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}QuoteChars@{fg text}
  S ISG

  @{fg shine}Raw@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}Text@{fg text}
  S ISG

  @{fg shine}Url@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}WordWrap@{fg text}
  B SG

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode

@Node MenuClass "RxMUI - Menu Class"


Menu class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "NotifyClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  Menustrip, Menu and Menuitem are used to create menus for
  applications and windows and context-menus for any object.

  A Menu can only be added to a Menustrip.

  A Menuitem named MI can only be added to:
     o a Menu
     o a Menuitem but if and only if MI has no child (Menuitems
       added to it)

  Once a Menustrip was used as strip for an application or a
  window it can't be removed or disposed.

  Once a Menustrip was used as context-menu for an object it
  can't be removed or disposed.

  To remove/dispose it you must set another Menustrip as
  context-menu for that object and then remove or dispose it.

  Of course all the above is handled by RxMUI: if something is
  not possible, RxMUI just returns an error code.

  See @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"} @{"Menuitem()" LINK "Menuitem"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Menuitem attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Checked@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}CheckIt@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}CommandString@{fg text}
  B ISG
  Set to 1 if the ShortCut (supplied directly or within the
  Title) is to be considered a description string. Note that if
  so, the string is not checked: this is left to you.

  @{fg shine}Enabled@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Exclude@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}MenuTrigger@{fg text}
  B GN
  Set to 1 and notified when a Menuitem is selected

  @{fg shine}ShortCut@{fg text}
  S ISG
  If CmdString is set to 1, this is just a description string,
  which is not checked by MUI, otherwise this is a
  real-one-char-short-cut.

  @{fg shine}Title@{fg text}
  S ISG
  It is the Menuitem title. If in the form S\Title, S is used as
  short cut for the Menuitem. Note that if ShortCut is supplied
  it is used, if \ is found, the short cut is ignored. This is
  very helpy in localizing strings.

  @{fg shine}Toggle@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Menuitem method@{ub}

  None defined

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Menu attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Enabled@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Title@{fg text}
  S ISG

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Menu methods@{ub}

  None defined

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Menustrip attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Enabled@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Menustrip methods@{ub}

  None defined

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Example@{ub}

    The following lines all create the same Menustrip object:

    1. Recursively
      app.Menustrip="mstrip"
       mstrip.0="mproject"
       mstrip.Class="Menustrip"
        mproject.Class="Menu"
        mproject.Title="Project"
         mproject.0="mabout"
          mabout.Class="Menuitem"
          mabout.title="About..."
          mabout.shortcut="?"
         mproject.1="maboutrxmui"
          maboutrxmui.Class="Menuitem"
          maboutrxmui.title="About RxMUI..."
         mproject.2="maboutmui"
          maboutmui.Class="Menuitem"
          maboutmui.title="About MUI..."
         mproject.3="md1"
          md1.Class="Menuitem"
          md1.title="BAR"
         mproject.4="mhide"
          mhide.Class="Menuitem"
          mhide.title="Hide"
          mhide.shortcut="H"
         mproject.5="md2"
          md2.Class="Menuitem"
          md2.title="BAR"
         mproject.6="mquit"
          mquit.Class="Menuitem"
          mquit.title="Quit"
          mquit.shortcut="Q"
       mstrip.1="meditor"
        meditor.Class="Menu"
        meditor.Title="Editor"
         meditor.0="mdefault"
          mdefault.Class="Menuitem"
          mdefault.title="Reset to defaults"
          mdefault.shortcut="R"
         meditor.1="mlast"
          mlast.Class="Menuitem"
          mlast.title="Last saveds"
          mlast.shortcut="L"
         meditor.2="mrestore"
          mrestore.Class="Menuitem"
          mrestore.title="Restore"
          mrestore.shortcut="R"
         meditor.3="md3"
          md3.Class="Menuitem"
          md3.title="BAR"
         meditor.4="mmui"
          mmui.Class="Menuitem"
          mmui.title="MUI..."

    2. Pre
      mstrip.0="mproject"
       mproject.Class="Menu"
       mproject.Title="Project"
        mproject.0=Menuitem("mabout","About...","?")
        mproject.1=Menuitem("maboutrxmui","About RxMUI...")
        mproject.2=Menuitem("maboutmui","About MUI...")
        mproject.3=Menuitem(,"BAR")
        mproject.4=Menuitem("mhide","Hide","H")
        mproject.5=Menuitem(,"BAR")
        mproject.6=Menuitem("mquit","Quit","Q")
      mstrip.1="meditor"
       meditor.Class="Menu"
       meditor.Title="Editor"
        meditor.0=Menuitem("mdefault","Reset to defaults","D")
        meditor.1=Menuitem("mlast","Last saveds","L")
        meditor.2=Menuitem("mrestore","Restore","R")
        meditor.3=Menuitem(,"BAR")
        meditor.4=Menuitem("mmui","MUI...")
      if NewObj("Menustrip","mstrip")>0 then exit
      ...
      app.Menustrip="mstrip"

    3. Mixed
      app.Menustrip="mstrip"
       mstrip.0="mproject"
       mstrip.Class="Menustrip"
        mproject.Class="Menu"
        mproject.Title="Project"
         mproject.0=Menuitem("mabout","About...","?")
         mproject.1=Menuitem("maboutrxmui","About RxMUI...")
         mproject.2=Menuitem("maboutmui","About MUI...")
         mproject.3=Menuitem(,"BAR")
         mproject.4=Menuitem("mhide","Hide","H")
         mproject.5=Menuitem(,"BAR")
         mproject.6=Menuitem("mquit","Quit","Q")
       mstrip.1="meditor"
        meditor.Class="Menu"
        meditor.Title="Editor"
         meditor.0=Menuitem("mdefault","Reset to defaults","D")
         meditor.1=Menuitem("mlast","Last saveds","L")
         meditor.2=Menuitem("mrestore","Restore","R")
         meditor.3=Menuitem(,"BAR")
         meditor.4=Menuitem("mmui","MUI...")

    4. MakeObj()
      app.Menustrip=MakeObj(,"Menustrip",,
          MakeObj(,"Menu","Project",,
              Menuitem("mabout","About...","?"),,
              Menuitem("maboutrxmui","About RxMUI..."),,
              Menuitem("maboutmui","About MUI..."),,
              Menuitem(,"BAR"),,
              Menuitem("mhide","Hide","H"),,
              Menuitem(,"BAR"),,
              Menuitem("mquit","Quit","Q")),,
          MakeObj("medit","Menu","Editor",,
              Menuitem("mdefault","Reset to defaults","D"),,
              Menuitem("mlast","Last saveds","L"),,
              Menuitem("mrestore","Restore","R"),,
              Menuitem(,"BAR"),,
              Menuitem("mmui","MUI...")))

@EndNode

