@Node NListClass "RxMUI - NList Class"


NList class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The NList class is used to manipulate lists.

  A NList object is not a NListview: it is the list that the
  NListview will render.

  A NList object can only be added to a NListview object at
  NListview creation time.

  NList class is a subclass of NList.mcc, so you must have
  NList.mmc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. Nlist.mcc is copyright of
  Gilles Masson.

  See @{"NListview" LINK "NListviewClass"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Active@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Off
     o Top
     o Bottom
     o Up
     o Down
     o PageUp
     o PageDown

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry@{fg text}
  S N
  As Active, but represents the contents of the entry

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry0@{fg text}
  S N
  The contents of the column number 0 of the active entry

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry1@{fg text}
  S N

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry2@{fg text}
  S N

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry3@{fg text}
  S N

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry4@{fg text}
  S N

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry5@{fg text}
  S N

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry6@{fg text}
  S N

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry7@{fg text}
  S N

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry8@{fg text}
  S N

  @{fg shine}ActiveEntry9@{fg text}
  S N

  @{fg shine}AdjustHeight@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}AdjustWidth@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}AutoCopyToClip@{fg text}
  B IS

  @{fg shine}AutoVisible@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}ButtonClick@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}Case@{fg text}
  B I
  Set comparation mode (0 is the default)

  @{fg shine}ClickColumn@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}DefaultInsertPos@{fg text}
  M IS
  A number or one of:
     o Active
     o Default (Default)
     o Bottom
     o Sorted
     o Top

  Entries supplied at Init time or via AddStem or ClearAddStem
  are inserted at this position. If this attribute is not
  supplied or its value is Default, entries are inserted:
     o Sorted - if DragSortable is 1
     o At the bottom - otherwise

  @{fg shine}DefaultObjectOnClick@{fg text}
  B IS

  @{fg shine}DefClickColumn@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}DoubleClick@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}DragColOnly@{fg text}
  N SG

  @{fg shine}DragSortable@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}DragSortInsert@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}DragType@{fg text}
  S ISG G2N
  One of:
     o None
     o Immediate
     o Borders
     o Qualifier
     o MultiSelect
     o None
     o Default
     o Shifted
     o Always

  @{fg shine}DropMark@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}DropType@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}Entries@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}EntryClick@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}First@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Top
     o Bottom
     o Up
     o Down
     o PageUp
     o PageDown

  @{fg shine}ForcePen@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}Format@{fg text}
  S ISG

  @{fg shine}HorizDeltaFactor@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}HorizEntries@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}HorizFirst@{fg text}
  N SGN

  @{fg shine}HorizVisible@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}Image@{fg text}
  S I
  See Images in lists

  @{fg shine}Input@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}InsertPosition@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}LineHeight@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}List@{fg text}
  S I
  A name of an ARexx stem where to read entries

  @{fg shine}ListviewTabSize@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}MinColCompare@{fg text}
  N I
  Specify the minimum column number that affects the sorting. It
  is specially usefull if the first column of the list contains
  an image specification.

  @{fg shine}MinColSortable@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}MinLineHeight@{fg text}
  N IS

  @{fg shine}MultiClick@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}MultiClickAlone@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}MultiSelect@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Names@{fg text}
  S I
  A string of entries separated by a ,

  @{fg shine}PropDeltaFactor@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}PropEntries@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}PropFirst@{fg text}
  N SGN

  @{fg shine}PropVisible@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}Quiet@{fg text}
  B SG

  @{fg shine}SelectChange@{fg text}
  B N

  @{fg shine}ShowDropMark@{fg text}
  B ISG
  For compatibility reasons, use ShowDropMarks

  @{fg shine}ShowDropMarks@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}SortFormat@{fg text}
  S ISG
  Here you may specify a sort Format String to control some
  sorting options. The string may contain one entry for each
  column of the list. Entries are seperated by commas, one entry
  is parsed via dos.library/ReadArgs().

  The template for a single entry is:
  C=COL/K/N,NUM/S,CASE/S

  where:

  o COL
    This value adjusts the number of the current column. Defaults
    to current entry number (0,1,...).

  o NUM
    An integral number comparation is to be applied to this
    column.

  o CASE
    A string case comparation is to be applied to this column.

  Note that:

  1. Default value is an empty string.

  2. If one column is omitted, it's value is cleared.

  3. Numeric comparation is also controlled by NumSort attribute.

  4. Case comparation is also controlled by Case attribute.

  5. Entries for columns that doesn't exist are ignored.

  Example:

  Let's suppose you created a List with 3 col, First, Second and
  Third, where First is to be nocase-sorted, Second is to be
  case-sorted and Third is to be num-sorted, just set (init)
  SortFormat to "CASE,,NUM"

  @{fg shine}SortType@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  A number or one of:
     o None
     o AddNone
     o Add2Values
     o Add4Values

  @{fg shine}SortType2@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}Title@{fg text}
  S IS

  @{fg shine}TitleClick@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}TitleClick2@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}TitleMark@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}TitleMark2@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}Visible@{fg text}
  N N

  @{fg shine}WrapCol@{fg text}
  N I

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AddStem@{fg text}
  <stemName/V>,[pos]
  Add the entries defined in stem to the list.
  mode
  is one of:
     o Active
     o Default
     o Bottom
     o Sorted
     o Top

  See DefaultInsertPos

  @{fg shine}Clear@{fg text}
  -
  Clear the list

  @{fg shine}ClearAddStem@{fg text}
  <stemName/V>,[pos]
  As AddStem, but clear the list before adding
  the entries.
  mode is one of:
     o Active
     o Default
     o Bottom
     o Sorted
     o Top

  See DefaultInsertPos

  @{fg shine}Exchange@{fg text}
  <entry1>,<entry2>
  Exchanges 2 entries

  entry1 is a number or one of:
     o Top
     o Active
     o Bottom

  entry2 is a number or one of:
     o Top
     o Active
     o Bottom
     o Next
     o Previous

  @{fg shine}GetEntries@{fg text}
  <stem>
  The method writes in stem.num the number of the entries and in
  stem.0,... stem.i (i=stem.num-1) the entries:
      DoMethod("list","GetEntries","entries")
      do i=0 to entries.num-1
          say entries.i
      end

  @{fg shine}GetEntry@{fg text}
  <pos>,<var>
  Get an entry

  pos is a number or Active

  @{fg shine}GetSelected@{fg text}
  <stem>
  The method writes in stem.num the number of the selected
  entries and in stem.0,... stem.i (i=stem.num-1) the entries:
      do i=0 to sel.num-1
          say sel.i
      end

  @{fg shine}Insert@{fg text}
  >entry>,[pos]
  Insert an entry.

  pos is a number or one of:
     o Active
     o Bottom (Default)
     o Sorted
     o Top

  @{fg shine}InsertWrap@{fg text}
  <entry>,[pos],[wrapcol],[align]
  Insert an entry.

  pos is a number or one of:
     o Active
     o Bottom (Default)
     o Sorted
     o Top

  wrapcol is a number or one of:
     o NoWrap
     o WrapCol0
     o WrapCol1
     o WrapCol2
     o WrapCol3
     o WrapCol4
     o WrapCol5
     o WrapCol6
     o Wrapped

  align is a number or one of:
     o Center
     o Justify
     o Left
     o Right

  @{fg shine}Jump@{fg text}
  [pos]
  Jump to an entry, making it visible

  pos is a number or one of:
     o Active (Default)
     o Bottom
     o Down
     o Top
     o Up

  @{fg shine}Remove@{fg text}
  [pos]
  Removes an entry

  pos is a number or:
     o Active (Default)
     o First
     o Last
     o Selected

  @{fg shine}ReplaceCol@{fg text}
  <pos>,<col>,<value>
  Replaces the col column of the pos entry with value .
  pos is a number or Active

  @{fg shine}Select@{fg text}
  [pos],[type],[var/S]
  Selects entries.

  pos is a number or one of:
     o Active (Default)
     o All

  val is a number or one of:
     o Ask
     o On
     o Off
     o Toggle (Default)

  If type is Ask the third argument must be supplied and must be
  a valid ARexx var name: it will contain the number of the
  selected entries.

  @{fg shine}Sort @{fg text}
  -
  Sort the entries of the list.

  @{fg shine}Sort2@{fg text}
  <type>,<add>
  Sorts the entries of the list.

  add is a number or one of:
     o None
     o AddNone
     o Add2Values
     o Add4Values

  Usually it is used to sort multicolumn list when the user
  click on title buttons:
      call Notify("list","TitleClick",
      "Everytime","list","Sort2","TriggerValue",
      "Add2Values")

  @{fg shine}Sort3@{fg text}
  <type>,<add>,<which>
  Sorts the entries of the list

  add is a number or one of:
     o None
     o AddNone
     o Add2Values
     o Add4Values

  which is a number or one of:
     o Type1
     o Type2
     o Both

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

  @{b}Insertion and sorting@{ub}

  Insertion means adding entries at init time and adding entries
  with AddStem and ClearAddStem methods.

  Insertion is ruled by the following attributes:
  o DefaultInsertPos
  o DragSortable

  At init time, if DefaultInsertPos is specified ad it is not
  Default, entries are inserted at the position there specified,
  otherwise if DragSortable is 1, entries are inserted Sorted,
  otherwise entries are inserted at the bottom.

  The above applies as well, when adding entries with AddStem and
  ClearAddStem.

  Sorting is ruled by the following attributes:
  o SortType
  o SortType2
  o SortFormat

 SortType specifies the main sorting criterium: no sort, the
 number of the column that rules the sort, a reverse order.

 If SortType cannot decide the order of two entries, SortType2 is
 used: it specifies a secondary sorting criterium; it has the
 same values of SortType, but regarding a different column.

 SortFormat specifies options for each column of the list.

 Note that SortType and SortType2 default values are OFF. It
 means that no sorting applies and entries are inserted not
 sorted (usually at the bottom), despite the value of
 DefaultInserPos.

@EndNode

@Node NListtreeClass "RxMUI - NListtree Class"


NListtree class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "NListClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The NListtree class is used to manipulate trees of lists.

  A NListtree object can only be added to a NListview object at
  NListview creation time.

  Despite NListtree class is declared to be subclass of NList
  class, no NList attribute and method may be used with a
  NListtree object.

  NListtree is a subclass of NListtree.mcc so you must have
  NListtree.mcc in MUI:libs/mui to use it. NListtree.mcc is
  copyright of Carsten Scholling.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}ActiveID@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  This attribute indicates the active entry in a NListtree. The
  possible values are non negative integer, where 0 means no
  active entry, >0 means there is an active entry. Note that any
  reference to an entry is made by ActiveID !!!.

  @{fg shine}ActiveList@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}ActiveName@{fg text}
  S ISGN

  @{fg shine}AutoVisible@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Off
     o Normal
     o FirstOpen
     o Expand

  @{fg shine}DoubleClick@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Off
     o All
     o Tree
     o NoTrigger

  @{fg shine}DragDropSort@{fg text}
  B IS

  @{fg shine}DragSortable@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}DropTarget@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}DropType@{fg text}
  S GN
  One of:
     o Above
     o Below
     o Onto
     o Sorted
     o None

  @{fg shine}EmptyNodes@{fg text}
  B IS

  @{fg shine}Format@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}MultiSelect@{fg text}
  M I
  A number or one of:
     o None
     o Default
     o Shifted
     o Always

  @{fg shine}Quiet@{fg text}
  B IS

  @{fg shine}ShowTree@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Title@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}TreeColumn@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}Visible@{fg text}
  N N

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Clear@{fg text}
  -
  Clear the whole NListtree.

  @{fg shine}Close@{fg text}
  [list],[what]
  Closes an entry.

  Arguments:
     o list - the list to close; a positive integral number or
       one of:
        o Active (default)
        o Parent
        o Root
     o what - what to close; one of:
        o Active (Default)
        o All
        o Head
        o Tail

  @{fg shine}FindName@{fg text}
  <var>,<name>,[list],[flags]
  Gets an entry by name.

  Arguments:
     o var - where to store results
     o name - the name of the entry to find
     o list - where to search; a positive integral number or one
       of:
        o Active
        o Root (Default)
     o flags - one or more of:
        o Activate
        o SameLevel
        o Selected
        o StartNode
        o Visible

  @{fg shine}GetEntry@{fg text}
  <var>,[id],[flags]
  Gets an entry by id.

  Arguments:
     o var - where to store results
     o id - a positive integral number or Active (Default)
     o flags - one or more of:
        o SameLevel
        o Visible

  The method writes in var the entry and in the fields:
     o .Frozen
     o .List
     o .NoSign
     o .Open
     o .Selected
  an ARexx boolean

  @{fg shine}GetEntry2@{fg text}
  <var>,[id],[pos],[flags]
  Relative-gets an entry by id.

  Arguments:
     o var - where to store results
     o id - a positive integral number or one of:
        o Active
        o Root (Default)
     o pos - id-relative position of the node to get; one of:
        o Head (Default)
        o Tail
        o Active
        o Next
        o Previous
        o Parent
     o flags - one or more of:
        o SameLevel
        o Visible

  The method writes in var the entry and in the fields:
     o .Frozen
     o .List
     o .NoSign
     o .Open
     o .Selected
  an ARexx boolean

  @{fg shine}GetSelected@{fg text}
  <var>
  Gets the list of the selected entries.

  Arguments:
     o var - where to store results

  The method writes in var.num the number of the selected entries
  and in var.0,... var.i (i=var.num-1) the entries:
      do i=0 to sel.num-1
          say sel.i
      end

  @{fg shine}Insert@{fg text}
  <entry>,[list],[prev],[flags],[name]

  Arguments:
     o entry - the entry to insert
     o list - the node which list is used to insert the entry; a
       positive integral number or one of:
        o Root
        o Active
        o ActiveFallBack (Default)
        o LastInserted
     o prev - the node which is the predecessor of the node to
       insert; a positive integral number or one of:
        o Head
        o Tail
        o Active (Default)
        o Sorted
     o flags - one or more of:
        o Open
        o List
        o Frozen
        o NoSign
        o Active
        o NextNode
     o name - the name of the entry

  @{fg shine}Open@{fg text}
  [list],[what]
  Opens an entry.

  Arguments:
     o list - the list to open; a positive integral number or one
       of:
        o Active (default)
        o Parent
        o Root
     o what - what to open; one of:
        o Active (Default)
        o All
        o Head
        o Tail

  @{fg shine}Remove@{fg text}
  [id],[what]
  Removes and entry.

  Arguments:
     o id - the entry to remove; a positive integral number or one of:
        o Active
        o Root (default)
     o what - what to remove with id; one of:
        o Active
        o All
        o Head
        o Tail

  Note that if what is not supplied, all id is removed.

  @{fg shine}Select@{fg text}
  [id],[selType]
  Selects entries.

  Arguments:
     o id - the entry to select; a positive integral number or
       one of:
        o Active (default)
        o All
        o Visible
     o selType - one of:
        o Off
        o On (Default)
        o Toggle

  @{fg shine}Sort@{fg text}
  [id],[flags]
  Sorts entries.

  Arguments:
     o id - what to sort; a positive integral number or one of:
        o Active
        o ActiveList
        o Root (default)
     o flags - one of:
        o All
        o Open

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Examples@{ub}

  1. Static creation
     list.Frame="InputList"
     list.Format="BAR,"
     list.Title="Name|Phone"
      list.0="Friends"; list.0.list="am"
       am.0="Frank|0864845111"; am.0.name="Frank"
       am.2="University"; am.2.name="uni"; am.2.type="tree"; am.2.list="uni"
        uni.0="Mary"; uni.0.name="Mary"
        uni.1="Jhon"
        uni.2="Profs"; uni.2.flags="list"
       am.1="Robert"
      list.1="Computer Shop"

  2. Dynamic insertion
     list.Frame="InputList"
     list.Format="BAR,"
     list.Title="Name|Phone"
     ...
     call set("list","Quiet",1)
     call DoMethod("list","Insert","Friends","root",,"List"); friends=rc
      call DoMethod("list","Insert","Franck|0864845111",friends,,,"A")
      call DoMethod("list","Insert","University",friends,,"List","uni"); uni=rc
       call DoMethod("list","Insert","Mary",uni,,,"Mary")
       call DoMethod("list","Insert","Jhon",uni)
       call DoMethod("list","Insert","Profs",uni,,"list")
      call DoMethod("list","Insert","Robert",friends)
     call DoMethod("list","Insert","Computer Shop","root")
     call set("list","Quiet",0)

  3. How to get all the entries of a NListtree (with its structure)
     call printList("root",0)
     ...
     printList: procedure
     parse arg l,s
         call DoMethod("Listtree","GetEntry2","e",l,"head")
         do while rc
             say copies(" ",s) || "Name:"e.name "Value:"e "ID:"e.id "IsList:"e.list
             if e.list then call printList(e.id,s+1)
             call DoMethod("Listtree","GetEntry2","e",e.id,"next")
         end
         return

@EndNode

@Node NListviewClass "RxMUI - NListview Class"


NListview class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "GroupClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The NListview class is used to create Listview.

  A NListview object is not a list: it is the object that renders
  a NList object.

  Once you created a NListview object, you can set/get any
  attribute and use any method of the NList object directly to
  the NListview.

  NListview class is a subclass of NListview.mcc, so you must
  have NListview.mmc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. Nlistview.mcc is
  copyright of Gilles Masson.

  See @{"NList" LINK "NListClass"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AutoDefault@{fg text}
  B I
  Set the DefaultObject of the window the object belongs to this
  NListview. Usefull when the NListview is in Popobject/Popstring

  @{fg shine}List@{fg text}
  S I
  The name of a NList object

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode

