@Node PopaslClass "RxMUI - Popasl Class"


Popasl class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "PopstringClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Popasl class is used to create an object made of a string
  object and a button.

  When the button is pressed, an asl.library requester is shown.
  The string contents is set to the selection made in the
  requester.

  Note that a Popasl object has no attribute to specify a key to
  open its requester. It may be specified via Window class
  InputEvent attribute, e.g.
      call Notify("win","InputEvent","ralt f","pop","Open")

  See @{"Popstring" LINK "PopstringClass"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Active@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}ButtonCycleChain@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1, the popup button will be in the window cycle
  chain.

  @{fg shine}IgnorePosition@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1, the requester ignores position and
  dimensions.

  @{fg shine}NegativeText@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}NotifyOnlyChanges@{fg text}
  S I
  Normally, the String object would notify NewContenyts anytime
  its Contents changes. This may be changed via AlwaysNotifyNC,
  but when a String object is used as String in a Popasl, it
  notifies its NewContents anytime it changes by default
  (AlwaysNotifyNC=1). Setting this attribute to 0 sets
  AlwaysNotifyNC of the String object to 1. Setting this
  attribute to 1 sets AlwaysNotifyNC of the String object to 0.

  @{fg shine}PopSpec@{fg text}
  M I
  An Image Spec for the pop button

  @{fg shine}PopToFront@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V44

  @{fg shine}PositiveText@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}RememberPosition@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1, the requester remembers position and
  dimensions.

  @{fg shine}SleepApplication@{fg text}
  B I
  If set 1, the application is put to sleep when the
  requester is active.

  @{fg shine}SleepWindow@{fg text}
  B I
  If set 1, the window is put to sleep when the requester is
  active.

  @{fg shine}String@{fg text}
  S I
  A String class object.

  @{fg shine}String@{fg text}
  S I
  A String class object.

  @{fg shine}Title@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Type@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o File
     o Font

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}File requester attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AcceptPattern@{fg text}
  S I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DoMultiSelect@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DoPatterns@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DoSaveMode@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DrawersOnly@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}FilterMacro@{fg text}
  S I
  At Init time you can define a filter-macro in this attribute:
  anytime the file requester should show an entry, that macro is
  called with 3 arguments:
    1. the name of the entry
    2. the name of the drawer
    3. a pointer to a FileInfoBlock structure relative to the entry

  If the macro fails or returns 1, the entry is showed, otherwise
  the entry is not showed. The macro must be an
  ARexx-in-line-string-macro designed to be fast.
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}FilterDrawers@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}Pattern@{fg text}
  S I
  asl.library V36

  @{fg shine}RejectIcons@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}RejectPattern@{fg text}
  S I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}ShowVolumes@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V44

  @{fg shine}SortBy@{fg text}
  M ISG
  A number or one of:
     o Date
     o Name
     o Size
  asl.library V44

  @{fg shine}SortDrawers@{fg text}
  M ISG
  A number or one of:
     o First
     o Last
     o Mix
  asl.library V44

  @{fg shine}SortOrder@{fg text}
  M ISG
  A number or one of:
     o Ascend
     o Descend
  asl.library V44

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Font requester attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}BackPen@{fg text}
  N I
  asl.library V36

  @{fg shine}DoBackPen@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DoDrawMode@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DrawMode@{fg text}
  S I
  A number or one of:
     o JAM1
     o JAM2
     o Complement
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DoFrontPen@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}DoStyle@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}FixedWidthOnly@{fg text}
  B I
  asl.library V38

  @{fg shine}Flags@{fg text}
  N I
  Initial requester flags.
  asl.library V36

  @{fg shine}FrontPen@{fg text}
  N I
  asl.library V36

  @{fg shine}MaxBackPen@{fg text}
  N I
  asl.library V40

  @{fg shine}MaxFrontPen@{fg text}
  N I
  asl.library V40

  @{fg shine}MaxHeight@{fg text}
  N I
  asl.library V40

  @{fg shine}MinHeight@{fg text}
  N I
  asl.library V40

  @{fg shine}SampleText@{fg text}
  B I
  May be set to a max 80 chars sample text to show. If empty, the
  default one is used.
  asl.library V45

  @{fg shine}Size@{fg text}
  N I
  asl.library V36

  @{fg shine}Style@{fg text}
  S I
  A number or one of:
     o Normal
     o Underline
     o Bold
     o Italic
  asl.library V36

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Note@{ub}

  Popstring Open method works with a Popasl object, but Close
  doesn't.

@EndNode

@Node PopobjectClass "RxMUI - Popobject Class"


Popobject class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "PopstringClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Popobject class is used to create an object made of:
     o a string object - a string object
     o a button object - a popup object or a button object
     o a object to open - a generic object to popup

  Any time the button is pressed a window with the object to open
  as content is opened.

  See @{"Popstring" LINK "PopstringClass.guide"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Button@{fg text}
  S I
  It may be omitted: a popup button is used

  @{fg shine}ButtonCycleChain@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1, the auto button will be in the window cycle chain

  @{fg shine}CloseFun@{fg text}
  S I

  At Init time you can supply a macro in this attribute: anytime
  the object is closed with success, CloseFun macro is executed
  (with no argument). The macro must be an
  ARexx-in-line-string-macro designed to be fast, e.g.
      "call DoMethod('l','GetEntry','active','A');call set('s','contents',a)"

  @{fg shine}Follow@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}Light@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}Object@{fg text}
  S IN

  @{fg shine}OpenFun@{fg text}
  S I
  At Init time you can supply a macro in this attribute: anytime
  the object is to be opened, OpenFun macro is executed (with no
  argument). The object is opened if and only if the macro
  returns 1. The macro must be an ARexx-in-line-string-macro
  designed to be very fast, e.g.
     "call domethod('l','clear');call set('l','quiet',1);pl=show('p',,'/');do while pl~='';parse var pl p '/' pl;call domethod('l','insert',p,'sorted');end;call set('l','quiet',0);return 1"

  @{fg shine}String@{fg text}
  S I IND
  A String class object .

  @{fg shine}Success@{fg text}
  B GN
  Set and notified when the window is closed with success. The
  popobject doesn't know anything about it: you must tell him
  what success means via a notify.

  @{fg shine}Toggle@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}Volatile@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode

@Node PopstringClass "RxMUI - Popstring Class"


Popstring class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "GroupClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Popstring class is used to create a popstring, which is an object made
  of:
     o a string object - a generic object
     o a button object - a generic object
     o a window object - a window object

  Any time the button object is "pressed" the window is opened.

  See @{"Popobject" LINK "PopobjectClass"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Button@{fg text}
  S I
  It may be omitted: a popup button is used

  @{fg shine}ButtonCycleChain@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1, the auto button will be in the window cycle chain

  @{fg shine}CloseFun@{fg text}
  S I
  At Init time you can supply a macro in this attribute: anytime
  the object is closed, CloseFun macro is executed with one
  argument: the success flag. The macro must be an
  ARexx-in-line-string-macro designed to be very fast.

  @{fg shine}Open@{fg text}
  B GN
  Set and notified when the window is opened/closed.

  @{fg shine}OpenFun@{fg text}
  S I
  At Init time you can supply a macro in this attribute: anytime
  the object is to be opened, OpenFun macro is executed (with no
  argument). The object is opened if and only if the macro
  returns 1. The macro must be an ARexx-in-line-string-macro
  designed to be very fast.

  @{fg shine}String@{fg text}
  S I IND
  A String class object.

  @{fg shine}Success@{fg text}
  B GN
  Set and notified when the window is closed. The popobject
  doesn't know anything about it: you must tell him what success
  means via a notify, e.g.:
      call Notify("pw","CloseRequest",1,"ps","Close",0)
      call Notify("cs","Pressed",0,"ps","Close",1)

  @{fg shine}Toggle@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}Window@{fg text}
  S I IND

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Close@{fg text}
  [success/N]
  success is an ARexx boolean. It is passed to CloseFun, if
  supplied.

  @{fg shine}Open@{fg text}
  -

@EndNode

