@Node SliderClass "RxMUI - Slider Class"


Slider class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "NumericClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Slider class is used to create sliders.

  See @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Format@{fg text}
  S I
  This is a string that defines the format of the slider label.
  Rules:
    1. The size of the string may be max 31 chars long
    2. The string may contain just one %ld (%lx)
    3. The string may contain any number of %%
    4. The string can't contain any %s
    5. If Stringify is present, it is used
    6. If Format is present, it is used
    7. If neither Stringify and Format are present, %ld is used

  @{fg shine}Horiz@{fg text}
  S ISGN

  @{fg shine}Stringify@{fg text}
  S I
  At Init time you can define a stringify-macro in this
  attribute: anytime the object feels it should draw itself, that
  macro is executed with one argument: the current Value. The
  result of the macro is used as label for the object. If the
  macro fails or it returns an empty string or it doesn't return
  anything, Value itself is used. The macro must be an
  ARexx-in-line-string-macro designed to be fast. A simple
  example is:
      nb.Stringify = "parse arg val;return 'Value is:" val"

  WARNING: YOU CAN'T USE ANY FUNCTION OR SET ANY ATTRIBUTE OR DO
  ANYTHING THAT MIGHT LOCK THE LAYERS INSIDE STRINGIFY (E.G. YOU
  CANNOT OPEN WINDOWS, OPEN REQUESTERS OR EVEN SAY THERE!)

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode

@Node SpeedBarClass "RxMUI - SpeedBar Class"


SpeedBar class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "GroupClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Speedbar class is used to create image buttons bars.

  Speedbar is a subclass of Speedbar.mcc so you must have
  Speedbar.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it.

  Note that Speedbar is a group and any attribute of Group class
  may be used with it.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

  Speedbar.rxmec is also an ARexx shared library.

  You don't have to worry about adding Speedbar.rxmec to the
  ARexx libraries list, because it is done automatically.

  @{b}SBNotify@{ub} - Adds a notification.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
  res = SBNotify(notifier,button,attr,value,target,method,parameters)
  <notifier/V>,<id/N>,<attr/V>,<value>,<target/V>,<method/V>,{parms}

  @{b}Function@{ub}
   Adds a notification from notifier, a Speedbar object button
   with id button, to target triggered by attr when it changes to
   value invoking method on target with parms.

   You may use this function only with Speedbar objects, when you
   want to set up a notify triggered by a Speedbar button.

   attr may be one of:
      o Disabled
      o Pressed
      o Selected
      o ShowMe
      o Timer

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
   notifier - the object that notifies
   id - the id of a button of the bar (0,...)
   attr - the attribute that triggers the notification
   value - the value of attr that causes the notification
   target - the target of the notification. Specials values are:
      o _app - the application notifier belongs to
      o _win - the window notifier belongs to
      o _self - notifier itself
   method - a valid an indirect method to invoke on target
   parms - parameters for method

  @{b}Result@{ub}
   res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

   The function may fail if:
   [NO_OBJ] notifier or target not found
   [NO_METHOD] method is not valid for target
   [METHOD_NONOTIFY] method is direct-only
   [BAD_NOTIFY] the notification can't be added for some reason

  @{b}See@{ub}
   @{"Notification" LINK "Notification"}

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Bar attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Active@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  This is the active button in a mutual exclude set of buttons.
  Note that if just one mutual exclude set is defined, this attribute may be
  used for notification of the active one; if more that one mutual exclude set
  is defined in the same Speedbar, this attribute reflects the last set active
  button in a set of mutual exclude buttons and notifications triggered by
  active buttons must be set up via the attribute Selected of any single
  button.

  @{fg shine}BarSpacer@{fg text}
  B IS
  Only valid for SpeedBar.mcc V12. Before V12 it is ignored. The
  Spacer is a special bar.

  @{fg shine}BorderLess@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  It is GN only with SpeedBar.mcc V12.1

  @{fg shine}EnableUnderscore@{fg text}
  B IS
  Only valid for SpeedBar.mcc V12. Before V12 it is ignored.
  Enable underscoring of label. Note that it may be set iff it
  was set to 1 at Init time.

  @{fg shine}ImagesDrawer@{fg text}
  S I
  Path to the drawer where images are.

  @{fg shine}LabelPosition@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Bottom
     o Top
     o Right
     o Left

  @{fg shine}Layout@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Left
     o Center
     o Right
     o Up
     o Down

  @{fg shine}NoBrushes@{fg text}
  B G
  If, for any reason, the image of a button can't be read, this
  attribute is set to 1 and the Speedbar falls back to Text
  ViewMode. RaisingFrame B ISGN It is GN only with SpeedBar.mcc
  V12.1

  @{fg shine}SBSameHeight@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}SBSameWidth@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}SmallImages@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  It is GN only with SpeedBar.mcc V12.1

  @{fg shine}Spacer@{fg text}
  S I
  Name of a datatype picture file to use as spacer.

  @{fg shine}Spread@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}StripUnderscore@{fg text}
  B I
  Drops the "_" in the text of the buttons. Default is 1.

  @{fg shine}Sunny@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  It is GN only with SpeedBar.mcc V12.1

  @{fg shine}ViewMode@{fg text}
  M ISG G2N
  A number or one of:
     o TextGFX
     o GFX
     o Text

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Buttons attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Exclude@{fg text}
  N I
  Mutual exclude mask. Note that more than one set of mutual
  exclude buttons may be specified in a single Speedbar. This
  attribute forces Flags to Immediate (Toggle is disabled)

  @{fg shine}Img@{fg text}
  S I
  Name of a datatype picture file or the string Spacer to add a
  space

  @{fg shine}Text@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Help@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Flags@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o Disabled
     o Selected
     o Immediate
     o Toggle

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}SBGet@{fg text}
  <id/N><attr>,<var/V>
  Reads the value of the attribute attr of the button id and
  writes it in var.

  attrs is one of:
     o Disabled
     o Selected
     o ShowMe

  @{fg shine}SBSet@{fg text}
  <id/N><attr>,<value/N>
  Sets the attr of the button id to value.

  attrs is one of:
     o Disabled
     o Selected
     o ShowMe

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Example@{ub}

      speedbar.SameSize=1
      speedbar.Horiz=1
      speedbar.RaisingFrame=0
      speedbar.Borderless=0
      speedbar.ImagesDrawer="Pics"
      speedbar.Spacer="Spacer"
      speedbar.StripUnderscore=1  /* Both so that if under V12, we don't */
      speedbar.EnableUnderscore=1 /* display trash                       */
       speedbar.0.Img="back.iff"
       speedbar.0.Text="Back"
       speedbar.1.Img="forward.iff"
       speedbar.1.Text="Forward"
       speedbar.2.Img="reload.iff"
       speedbar.2.Text="Reload"
       speedbar.2.Flags="Immediate"
       speedbar.3.Img="stop.iff"
       speedbar.3.Text="Stop"
       speedbar.4.Img="SPACER"
       speedbar.5.Img="home.iff"
       speedbar.5.Text="Home"
       speedbar.5.Flags="Immediate Selected"
       speedbar.5.Exclude=2**6
       speedbar.6.Img="find.iff"
       speedbar.6.Text="Find"
       speedbar.6.Flags="Immediate"
       speedbar.6.Exclude=2**5

@EndNode

@Node SpeedButtonClass "RxMUI - SpeedButton Class"


SpeedButton class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The SpeedButton class is a subclass of Area class and it is
  used to create very cute image buttons.

  Speedbutton is a subclass of Speedbutton.mcc so you must have
  Speedbutton.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}BorderLess@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 0 you get a button without borders

  @{fg shine}EnableUnderscore@{fg text}
  B IS
  If set to 1 you enable underscoring and key char. Note that it
  may be set iff it was set to 1 at Init time

  @{fg shine}Image@{fg text}
  S I
  Name of a picture file to load via datatypes

  @{fg shine}ImmediateMode@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1 you get an Immediate button

  @{fg shine}Label@{fg text}
  S I
  A text to use as label for the button

  @{fg shine}LabelPosition@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Bottom
     o Top
     o Right
     o Left

  @{fg shine}MinHeight@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1 the button is y-unlimited

  @{fg shine}MinWidth@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1 the button is x-unlimited

  @{fg shine}NoClick@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1 the button is no input

  @{fg shine}Raising@{fg text}
  B IS
  If set to 1 a frame will be drawn when the mouse is over the
  button. Use only iff Borderless is 1

  @{fg shine}SmallImage@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1 you get a scaled image (the factor of which is
  settable in MUI prefs/SpeedBar)

  @{fg shine}StripUnderscore@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1 the underscores will be stripped from the label

  @{fg shine}Sunny@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1 you get a gray scale image, colored when the mouse
  is over the object

  @{fg shine}ToggleMode@{fg text}
  B I
  If set to 1 you get a Toggle button

  @{fg shine}ViewMode@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number, or one of:
     o TextGfx (0)
     o Gfx (1)
     o Text (2)

  To modify it you must: InitChange the group the SpeedButton
  belongs to, set the attribute, ExitChange the group

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode

@Node StringClass "RxMUI - String Class"


String class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The String class is used to create simple string gadgets or a
  very big text input objects.

  If you want scroll bars around the string object, use the
  TextInputScroll class. It has the same attributes and methods
  of String class.

  String is a subclass of TextInput.mcc, so you must have
  TextInput.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. TextInput.mcc is
  copyright of Oliver Wagner.

  See @{"String()" LINK "String"} @{"MakeObj()" LINK "MakeObj"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Accept@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  Only the chars in this string will be accepted

  @{fg shine}Acknowledge@{fg text}
  B GN
  Notified (use Everytime) when the user press return in the
  object

  @{fg shine}AdvanceOnCR@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  Pressing return activate the next object in the cycle chain

  @{fg shine}AlwaysNotifyNC@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  Both NewContents and Integer (if IsNumeric is 1) are notified
  on Acknowledge if and only if its value changed (actual value
  is different from previous one). Setting to attribute to 1
  makes String class to notify NewContents and Integer anytime.

  @{fg shine}AttachedList@{fg text}
  S IS
  This the name of an already existing (N)Listview object.
  Up/down arrows pressed-event in the String object is sent to
  the Listview. Note that the Listview object can't be remove or
  disposed anymore.

  @{fg shine}AutoExpand@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Auto expand size when needed

  @{fg shine}BlinkRate@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Frequency of the blink of the cursor

  @{fg shine}BookMark1@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Set/Get the bookmark n.1

  @{fg shine}BookMark2@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Set/Get the bookmark n.2

  @{fg shine}BookMark3@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Set/Get the bookmark n.3

  @{fg shine}Changed@{fg text}
  B GN
  Notified when the contents changes

  @{fg shine}Contents@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  The contents of the string; notified whenever it changes

  @{fg shine}CursorPos@{fg text}
  N SGN
  Position of the cursor

  @{fg shine}CursorStyle@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}DefPopUp@{fg text}
  B I
  Set to 0 if you don't want the default context menu and/or you
  want to use your won one.

  @{fg shine}Editable@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If 0, the contents can't be modified

  @{fg shine}Format@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Left
     o Center
     o Right

  @{fg shine}Integer@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  The integer contents of the object; it has sense especially if
  IsNumeric is 1.

  @{fg shine}IsNumeric@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If set to 1 you get a numeric string object.

  @{fg shine}IsOld@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Lines@{fg text}
  N GN
  Notified when the number of the lines changes

  @{fg shine}MarkEnd@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  Set/Get the end of a block. May be the string NOMARK to delete
  the mark

  @{fg shine}MarkStart@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  Set/Get the start of a block May be the string NOMARK to delete
  the mark

  @{fg shine}MaxLen@{fg text}
  N ISG
  Max len (+1) in chars for the string. Default 79 (it means 78
  chars)

  @{fg shine}MaxLines@{fg text}
  N IG
  Max number of lines

  @{fg shine}MaxVal@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Max val for Integer

  @{fg shine}MinimumWidth@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Min width for the object

  @{fg shine}MinVal@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Min val for Integer

  @{fg shine}MultiLine@{fg text}
  B IG
  If set to 1, the object is multi line

  @{fg shine}NewContents@{fg text}
  S GN
  It is notified on Acknowledge

  @{fg shine}NoCopy@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Forbid to copy the contents (or part of it)

  @{fg shine}NoExtraSpacing@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}NoInput@{fg text}
  B IG
  No input gadget

  @{fg shine}Preparse@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  A pre parse text

  @{fg shine}ProhibitParse@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}Quiet@{fg text}
  B SGN

  @{fg shine}Reject@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  Chars in this string will be rejected

  @{fg shine}RemainActive@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  Remain active if the user presses return

  @{fg shine}ResetMarkOnCursor@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Secret@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  Don't show the contents (e.g. for passwords)

  @{fg shine}SetMax@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If set to 1, the object width is limited to its contents size.
  Default 0

  @{fg shine}SetMin@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If set to 1, the object minimum width is set to the contents
  size. Default 0

  @{fg shine}SetVMax@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If set to 0, the object is y-size unlimited. Default 1 SetVMin
  B ISGN If set to 0, the object y-size is set to its contents
  height. It has sense iff MultiLine is 1. Default 1

  @{fg shine}StringFont@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Normal
     o Fixed

  @{fg shine}Styles@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o None
     o MUI
     o IRC
     o EMail
     o HTML

  @{fg shine}SuggestParse@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}TabLen@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Tab len

  @{fg shine}Tabs@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A number or one of:
     o Ignore
     o Spaces
     o Disk

  @{fg shine}TopLine@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  The first visible line

  @{fg shine}UseWinBorder@{fg text}
  B I
  TextInputScroll only. Use window border scroller.

  @{fg shine}VertScrollerOnly@{fg text}
  B I
  TextInputScroll only. Do not show the horiz scroller

  @{fg shine}WordWrap@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  Controls word wrap mode.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AppendText @{fg text}
  <text>
  Append text to the object.

  @{fg shine}DoBottom@{fg text}
  -

  @{fg shine}DoBS@{fg text}
  -

  @{fg shine}DoBSSOL@{fg text}
  -

  @{fg shine}DoBSWord@{fg text}
  -

  @{fg shine}DoCopy@{fg text}
