@Node TextEditorClass "RxMUI - TextEditor Class"


TextEditor class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  TextEditor class is used to create fully featured text editor
  objects.

  TextEditor class is a subclass of TextEditor.mcc, so you must
  have TextEditor.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. TextEditor.mcc
  is copyright of Allan Odgaard.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AreaMarked@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}AutoClip@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Columns@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}Contents@{fg text}
  S ISG
  This is the content of the object. Note that when you get it,
  you always get a <65536 chars string, despite the real length
  of it

  @{fg shine}CursorX@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}CursorY@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}Error@{fg text}
  N GN
  You may find here the last error, one of:
     o 1 ClipboardIsEmpty: clipboard is empty
     o 2 ClipboardIsNotFTXT: clipboard doesn't contain text
     o 3 MacroBufferIsFull: not used
     o 4 MemoryAllocationFailed: not used
     o 5 NoAreaMarked: Block: operation invoked, but no area
       marked
     o 6 NoMacroDefined: not used
     o 7 NothingToRedo: there is nothing to redo
     o 8 NothingToUndo: there is nothing to undo
     o 9 NotEnoughUndoMem: a block was erased but there is not
       enogh mem to save it for undo operation
     o 10 StringNotFound: not used
     o 11 NoBookmarkInstalled
     o 12 BookmarkHasBeenLost

  @{fg shine}Export@{fg text}
  S IS
  One of:
     o Plain
     o EMail

  @{fg shine}ExportWrap@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}FixedFont@{fg text}
  B IGN

  @{fg shine}Flow@{fg text}
  M SGN
  A number or one of:
     o Left
     o Right
     o Center
     o Justified (not implemented yet)

  @{fg shine}HasChanged@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Import@{fg text}
  S IS
  One of:
     o Plain
     o EMail
     o Mime
     o MimeQuoted

  @{fg shine}ImportWrap@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}InsertMode@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}InVirtualGroup@{fg text}
  B I
  Set it to 1 if your TextEditor is (supposed to be) in a
  Virtgroup

  @{fg shine}Pen@{fg text}
  N SGN

  @{fg shine}Quiet@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}ReadOnly@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}RedoAvailable@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}Rows@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}Separator@{fg text}
  S SG

  @{fg shine}Slider@{fg text}
  S I
  The name of a slider, prop, Scrollbar object to be linked to
  the TextEditor.
  Example:
  mgroup.0="teg"
   teg.class="group"
   teg.horiz=1
   teg.spacing=0
    teg.0="te"
     te.class="texteditor"
     te.slider="tescr"
      tescr.class="Scrollbar"
    teg.1="tescr"

  @{fg shine}StyleBold@{fg text}
  B SGN

  @{fg shine}StyleItalic@{fg text}
  B SGN

  @{fg shine}StyleUnderline@{fg text}
  B SGN

  @{fg shine}TypeAndSpell@{fg text}
  N SGN

  @{fg shine}UndoAvailable@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}WrapBorder@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}ARexxCmd@{fg text}
  <cmd>,[result/S]
  Execute the ARexx command cmd
  If result is supplied, it is used to store the result of the
  command, if any.

  @{fg shine}BlockInfo {fg text}
  <stem/V>
  The fields of stem set are:
     o StartX
     o StartY
     o StopX
     o StopY

  @{fg shine}ClearText@{fg text}
  -

  @{fg shine}FreeResources@{fg text}
  -
  When you get the contents of the object, a large amount of mem
  (depending of contents size) is allocated (and freed only at
  object disposing). To free this mem, you may use this method.

  @{fg shine}Insert@{fg text}
  <file>,[where]
  where is one of:
     o Cursor (default)
     o Top
     o Bottom
  Note that RC will contain the IoErr()

  @{fg shine}InsertText@{fg text}
  <text>,[where]
  where is one of:
     o Cursor (default)
     o Top
     o Bottom

  @{fg shine}MarkText@{fg text}
  <StartX>,<StartY>,<StopX>,<StopY>

  @{fg shine}Open@{fg text}
  <file>
  Note that RC will contain the IoErr()

  @{fg shine}Replace@{fg text}
  <string>

  @{fg shine}Save@{fg text}
  <file>

  @{fg shine}Search@{fg text}
  <string>,[flags]
  flags is one or more of:
     o Top
     o Case

@EndNode

@Node ToolbarClass "RxMUI - Toolbar Class"


Toolbar class    @{"Index" link "Classes"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Toolbar class is used to create image buttons bars.

  Toolbar is a subclass of Toolbar.mcc so you must have
  Toolbar.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI to use it. Toolbar.mcc is copyright
  of Benny Kjćr Nielsen.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

  Toolbar.rxmec is also an ARexx shared library.

  You don't have to worry about adding Toolbar.rxmec to the ARexx
  libraries list, because it is done automatically.

  @{b}TBNotify@{ub} - Adds a notification.

  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
  res = TBNotify(notifier,button,attr,value,target,method,parameters)
  <notifier/V>,<id/N>,<attr/V>,<value>,<target/V>,<method/V>,{parms}

  @{b}Function@{ub}
   Adds a notification from notifier, a Toolbar object button
   with id button, to target triggered by attr when it changes to
   value invoking method on target with parms.

   You may use this function only with Toolbar objects, when you
   want to set up a notify triggered by a Toolbar button.

   attr may be one of:
      o Active
      o Ghosted
      o Gone
      o Pressed

  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
   notifier - the object that notifies
   id - the button id of the bar
   attr - the attribute that triggers the notification
   value - the value of attr that causes the notification
   target - the target of the notification. Specials values are:
      o _app - the application notifier belongs to
      o _win - the window notifier belongs to
      o _self - notifier itself
   method - a valid an indirect method to invoke on target
   parms - parameters for method

  @{b}Result@{ub}
   res - 0 for success or >0 for failure

   The function may fail if:
   [NO_OBJ] notifier or target not found
   [NO_METHOD] method is not valid for target
   [METHOD_NONOTIFY] method is direct-only
   [BAD_NOTIFY] the notification can't be added for some reason

  @{b}See@{ub}
   @{"Notification" LINK "Notification"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Bar attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Description@{fg text}
  S I
  ARexx stem name, list of the buttons. If not supplied it is
  considered to be the object stem.

  @{fg shine}Help@{fg text}
  S GN

  @{fg shine}Horiz@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}ImageGhost@{fg text}
  S I
  Name of the ghosted images file.

  @{fg shine}ImageNormal@{fg text}
  S I
  Name of the normal images file.

  @{fg shine}ImageSelect@{fg text}
  S I
  Name of the selected images file.

  @{fg shine}Path@{fg text}
  S I
  Path to the images files. If supplied, images files are
  considered relative to this path.

  @{fg shine}Qualifier@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Buttons attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Exclude@{fg text}
  N I
  Mutual exclude mask. E.g. if button 10 excludes buttons 4 and
  9, button 10 Exclude is 2**4+2**9

  @{fg shine}Flags@{fg text}
  S I
  One or more of:
     o Ghosted
     o Gone
     o Radio
     o Selected
     o Toggle

  @{fg shine}Help@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Text@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Type@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o Button
     o Ignore
     o Space

  @{fg shine}Path@{fg text}
  S I
  Path to the images files. If supplied, images file are
  considered relative to this path.

  @{fg shine}Reusable@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Description@{fg text}
  S I
  ARexx stem name, list of the buttons. If not supplied it is
  considered to be the object stem.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}TBKillNotify@{fg text}
  -
  Use this instead of KillNotify()

  @{fg shine}TBreload@{fg text}
  <ImageNormal/N>,<ImageSelect>,<ImageGhost>
  Changes images

  @{fg shine}TBSet@{fg text}
  <id/N>,<what>,<value/N>
  Sets what of button id to value.
  what is one of:
     o Ghosted
     o Gone
     o Selected

  @{fg shine}TBSetAll@{fg text}
  <what>,<value/N>
  Sets what of all the buttons to value.
  what is one of:
     o Ghosted
     o Gone
     o Selected

@EndNode

